\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Select the Rest Tool.  Click on a staff to place the rest where the pointer is.  \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Rest placement \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 As for any staff object, rests are automatically placed when the system is adjusted (see Adjustment).  Rests may be moved to an alternative staff degree by ALT-dragging.  To  do this, select the rest, and holding down the Alt key, hold the mouse button down to drag the rest to a desired location.  The rest attaches itself to the nearest staff. \par
