\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 When a rest is selected, its attributes will be displayed by the inspector.  Any attribute can be changed, and the changes will take effect when the \i0\b0\f1\fs24 S\f1 ET\f0  button is pressed.  The Rest Inspector is sensitive to multiple selections.  See index entries on `multiple selection' for explanation.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 B\f1 ars Rest\f0 :  The textbox specifies the number of bars rest \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 D\f1 uration\f0 :  Specifies the duration of the rest. This attribute may also be modified with a keyboard equivalent.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 D\f1 ots\f0 :  Specifies the number of dots associated with the duration of the rest.  The blank button means no dots.  This attribute may also be modified with a keyboard equivalent.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 L\f1 ocked\f0 :  If checked, the rest will remain attached to its staff no matter how far away it is dragged with the mouse.  If not checked, a rest is unlocked: it will attach itself to the nearest staff when it is dragged.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 T\f1 imed Back\f0 :  Timed-back is used in late entry situations where it is convenient to time notes back from the barline at the end of the measure.  For explanation of use see index entries under `multiple voice notation' and `late entry'.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 T\f1 ight\f0 :  Specifies that the note is to be followed by less than the normal amount of spacing.  This is not generally useful, as most need for non-standard spacing (\i e.g.\i0  sesquialtera, coloured notation) are met by changing the proportionality of the governing time signature (see \b Time Signature\b0 ).\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 S\f1 tyle\f0 :  Specifies the graphic style of the rest.  The choices are (from left to right): Modern, Old Book, Bars Rest (number above), Bars Rest (number below), vertical bar (`binary' notation), whole bar rest, repeat sign.  The whole bar rest is useful when you wish to indicate a whole rest that has a duration other than a semibreve.  Both the whole bar rest and the repeat sign need to have a duration defined.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 V\f1 oice\f0 :  Specifies the voice number of the rest.  The default is voice 0.\par
